    "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nWhen `with cython.nogil(PARAM):` is used, the `PARAM` is ignored and GIL is release in any case - see the example. The example produces following code:\r\n<img width=\"293\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/827060/200083858-ab281c56-5d4a-407d-8413-41ddc92a0eec.png\">\r\n\r\nOn the other hand in the Cython syntax the parameter is not ignored and providing `True` in the example, the lock is not relased:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ndef increment(int x):\r\n    with nogil(False):\r\n        x = x + 1\r\n    return x\r\n\r\nprint(increment(5))\r\n```\r\n\r\n<img width=\"230\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/827060/200084085-36d5b338-6b6a-4820-aa47-cd116b6d4197.png\">\r\n\r\nThis behavior contradicts the documentation here:\r\nhttps://cython.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/tutorial/pure.html#managing-the-global-interpreter-lock\r\n\r\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\nimport cython\r\n\r\ndef increment(x: cython.int):\r\n    with cython.nogil(False):\r\n        x = x + 1\r\n    return x\r\n\r\nprint(increment(5))\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nOne of following:\r\n\r\n1. Pure version has same behaviour as Cython one\r\n2. Documentation is fixed\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\nOS: macOS\r\nPython version 3.9\r\nCython version master\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n`cython.gil()` seems to be also (at least partially affected/broken:\r\n* In cython following code generates C code:\r\n```cython\r\ndef increment(int x):\r\n    with nogil(False):\r\n        x = x + 1\r\n        with gil(False):\r\n            print(x)\r\n    return x\r\n\r\nprint(increment(5))\r\n```\r\n\r\n> Note: Also works for providing `True` instead of `False` to `gil`/`nogil`\r\n\r\nOn the other hand following code fails to compile:\r\n```cython\r\nimport cython\r\n\r\ndef increment(x: cython.int):\r\n    with cython.nogil(True):\r\n        x = x + 1\r\n        with cython.gil(True):\r\n            print(x)\r\n    return x\r\n\r\nprint(increment(5))\r\n```\r\nFor both `True`/`False` parametrers in `cython.gil`, `cython.nogil`\r\n\r\nOn the other hand following code works:\r\n```python\r\nimport cython\r\n\r\ndef increment(x: cython.int):\r\n    with cython.nogil:\r\n        x = x + 1\r\n        with cython.gil:\r\n            print(x)\r\n    return x\r\n\r\nprint(increment(5))\r\n```",
